additional_context.raw_instruction: Deploy my project to Google Cloud

infrastructure.recommended_path: Baseline GCP App Engine (Flex-ready) with Cloud Build CI and Cloud Run option
rationale: Codebase is unanalyzed with no declared language, frameworks, or containerization. Need low-friction, language-agnostic entry.
App Engine Standard can be used if language is supported; App Engine Flex or Cloud Run if custom runtime or later containerization is needed.
No HA/cost/compliance constraints; start simple, pay-per-use, minimal ops.
Serverless is false in input, but without infra details, managed PaaS (App Engine) or container (Cloud Run) is the safest baseline; we keep serverless features optional.

steps: Run local scan to detect primary language, framework, entrypoint, and dependencies.
Identify start command (e.g., npm start, gunicorn app:app, uvicorn main:app, java -jar app.jar, go run main.go).
Determine if static frontend vs API or monolith.
List required environment variables and secrets.
gcp_actions: Enable required APIs: cloudresourcemanager.googleapis.com, iam.googleapis.com, appengine.googleapis.com, cloudbuild.googleapis.com, artifactregistry.googleapis.com, secretmanager.googleapis.com, run.googleapis.com, logging.googleapis.com, monitoring.googleapis.com.
Select region (default to us-central1 if unspecified) and create App Engine app: gcloud app create --region=us-central.
Create Artifact Registry repo for future containers: gcloud artifacts repositories create app-repo --repository-format=docker --location=us-central1 --description='App images'

option_A_AppEngine_Standard_or_Flex.when_to_use: If language is one of App Engine Standard runtimes (Python, Node.js, Go, Java, PHP, Ruby) choose Standard. If custom runtime or non-supported version, choose Flex.
files: app.yaml with runtime or flexible runtime configuration
Optional: dispatch.yaml for routing, cron.yaml, queue.yaml as needed
notes: Auto-scaling and health checks are managed.
Simple path to custom domains, traffic splitting, versions, and revisions.

option_B_Cloud_Run_prep_for_future_conta.when_to_use: If you need custom binaries, background tasks, or plan to containerize soon.
steps: Add minimal Dockerfile for detected language once analysis is done.
Build and push image via Cloud Build: gcloud builds submit --tag us-central1-docker.pkg.dev/PROJECT_ID/app-repo/app:latest
Deploy to Cloud Run: gcloud run deploy app --image us-central1-docker.pkg.dev/PROJECT_ID/app-repo/app:latest --region=us-central1 --allow-unauthenticated

env: Store secrets in Secret Manager; reference in App Engine/Cloud Run via environment variables.
Non-secret config in app.yaml (env_variables) or Cloud Run --set-env-vars.

phased_strategy.ingress: Default public ingress. If private, use Serverless VPC Access for Cloud Run or App Engine VPC connectors.
phased_strategy.domains_tls: Map custom domain via App Engine/Cloud Run domain mappings; managed TLS.
phased_strategy.egress_control: If needed, configure egress via VPC connector and Cloud NAT.

phased_strategy.logging_metrics: Use Cloud Logging and Monitoring; add basic uptime checks and alerts in Cloud Monitoring.

cloud_build: Create cloudbuild.yaml with steps: test, build (if container), deploy (gcloud app deploy or gcloud run deploy).
Connect GitHub/GitLab repo to Cloud Build triggers for main and feature branches.
phased_strategy.policy: Require successful build/tests before deploy to prod; use App Engine traffic splitting or Cloud Run revisions for canaries.

scaling.recommendation: Start with automatic scaling; set min instances to 0 for cost control; tune concurrency for Cloud Run if used.

data_services.databases: Undeclared. Choose Cloud SQL (Postgres/MySQL) for relational or Firestore for serverless NoSQL; add VPC connector if private.
data_services.storage: Use Cloud Storage for static assets and uploads.

security.identity: Use Workload Identity Federation for CI and service-account-per-service.
security.iam: Principle of least privilege; restrict deployer roles to CI SA.

cost_controls.budgets: Set budgets and alerts in Cloud Billing.
cost_controls.autoscaling: Min instances 0, configure request timeouts appropriately.

infrastructure.next_steps_prompt: Provide repository or primary language/framework so we can generate exact app.yaml or Dockerfile and the cloudbuild.yaml.
